The Nigeria Cricket Federation has invited 40 female players to camp in preparation for the country’s participation in the Bilateral Series with Rwanda National Team scheduled to hold in Kigali from June 4 to 13, The PUNCH reports. In a letter signed by the federation’s Secretary-General, Taiwo Oriss, on Tuesday and made available to The PUNCH, the players are to arrive at the Goodluck Jonathan High-Performance Hostel MKO Abiola Stadium, Package B on May 10. Matches start on May 11 and run till May 16, when the camping ends. The 40 players were selected from across the country, with Edo having the highest number of invited players – 12. Kaduna and Akwa Ibom both have five players, while four players were invited from Kwara. Lagos and Ebonyi both have three players each invited for the trial, while Oyo, Plateau and Ogun had two players invited. Anambra and Cross River have one player each. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com